s become indissoluble from contemporary social imaginaries and how these gangs provide cover for a host of other criminal actors. Ethnographically rich and unflinchingly critical, Mortal Doubt illuminates the maras’ role in making and mooring collective terror in Guatemala City while tracing the ties that bind this violence to those residing in far safer environs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGangszGuatemalazGuatemala. 0aViolencezGuatemalazGuatemala. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  abrutal organizations.  acollective terror.  acontract killings.  acriminals.  adrug trade.  aextortion.  agang dominated neighborhoods.  agang violence.  agangs.  aguatemala city.  aguatemalans.  ainsecure life.  amaras.  amigration.  anew era of violence.  apolice precincts.  apostwar violence.  aprisons.  asocial order.  astate terror.  aus deportation.  aviolent crime.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029709840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096959940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969599423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520969599/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles